definitions.definition: A country consisting of the western part of the Samoan archipelago in Polynesia , in Oceania . Official name: Independent State of Samoa . Capital and largest city: Apia . Formerly Western Samoa , and, before that, German Samoa . It is distinct from American Samoa .
A census-designated place in Humboldt County , California , United States .
